reviews.text: Both pasta and pizza are tasty. Mocha is good. The environment is peaceful so you can enjoy food quietly. Very polite staff. Worth a try!

Bought some cakes for co-workers and friends! They loved it! We got hazelnut chocolate, chocolate truffle with blood orange 🍊, chamomile, lime, peach 🍑. The prices range are $36-52. The taste is rich especially chocolate flavor.
The cakes are not fresh and you can tell they have been in the fridge for days.

result.name: Paradise Mall

reviews.text:
There's a sports equipment outlet in the mall. There are a variety of restaurants, but personally I don't really like them. 梅光軒, 八方雲集, Paradise is good though. 😅

The mall is linked with the MTR mall, and it's close to the playgrounds nearby. 😀

Quiet a range of food and clothing choices, with very spatial, comfortable circulation. Paid a short visit with my family at a Chinese Restaurant. Happy with there quality food at a very affordable price. It could have been better with a wider selection of dim sum.

The top floors are outlets of sports shoes and fashion.  You can find most brands here.  Some offers bulk discounts from time to time and the merchandise can become extraordinary inexpensive subject to you buying lots lots lots.
This is a all-round mall with all kinds of shops. A few outlet shops there and the only indoor bouldering gym in a mall in HK makes this mall worth going

Truly like a paradis with many goody shops and a Tao Heung restaurant where I eat fatty beef, fish ball, sausage, luncheon meat, shrimp, dumpling, pork slice, noodol, ouster, clam (ent), wif garlic, chiuchow chili, soy sauce and some paste with 2 Pepsi. But no beer. Enjoy a calebrating time with friends

reviews.text: Lived here for 12 years. A quiet place with a nice sea view. I love watching the boats and ships in the sea. However, every time when there's a powerful typhoon, there's got to be some damage dealt to Heng Fa Chuen. But overall, this is a very good housing estate.
A very good community with a shopping mall linked with the MTR station. 😀
A self contained, quiet and pleasant living area.
Lived there for 9 years. Nice quiet estate close to MTR. Great for family with kids. Downside is it is very humid and for those blocks near the seaside were hit hard during typhoons.
lowkey good place for scuba diving during typhoon
